genresAdvancedInfo.name: dutch folk
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre is rooted in the traditional music of the Netherlands, and it often features acoustic instruments like the accordion, violin, and guitar. Dutch folk music is characterized by its simple and melodic structures, and it often tells stories of everyday life and rural culture. It can be both upbeat and melancholic, and it is often played at social gatherings like weddings and festivals.
